      <hedline>
        <hl1>Best Buy Selects Agency for Web Site</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Best Buy names units of DDB Worldwide, part of Omnicom Group, to handle account of its electronic-commerce Web site; billings estimated at $50 million (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Best Buy has named units of DDB Worldwide, part of the Omnicom Group, to handle the account of its electronic-commerce Web site. Billings were estimated at $50 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Best Buy has named units of DDB Worldwide, part of the Omnicom Group, to handle the account of its electronic-commerce Web site. Billings were estimated at $50 million.</p>
        <p>Laurie Bauer, a spokeswoman for Best Buy in Minneapolis, said the decision came after a six-month review that had been narrowed to DDB and Grey Advertising in New York. The DDB New York office will handle the account along with siblings like DDB Digital and DDB Downtown. Offline advertising for Best Buy continues to be handled in-house.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
